text: "Wow" is a 2008 song by Australian singer Kylie Minogue and is the third single from her 10th studio album X. It went to number 2 in Scotland, number 5 in the United Kingdom, number 10 in Ireland, number 11 in Australia, number 15 in France, number 19 in Hungary and Slovakia, number 29 in Finland, number 36 in the Netherlands and number 41 in Germany. ==Formats and track listings== UK CD single # "Wow" - 3:10 # "Cherry Bomb" - 4:16 UK CD maxi single / Australia CD maxi single # "Wow" — 3:13 # "Do It Again" — 3:21 # "Carried Away" — 3:14 # "Wow" (Death Metal Disco Scene Mix) — 6:27 UK 12" picture disc # "Wow" — 3:13 # "Wow" (CSS Mix) — 3:14 # "Wow" (F*** Me I'm Famous Remix by David Guetta & Joachim Garraud) - 6:22 # "Wow" (MSTRKRFT Remix) - 4:45 EU CD maxi single # "Wow" — 3:16 # "Wow" (Death Metal Disco Scene Mix) — 6:27 # "Wow" (CSS Mix) — 3:14 # "Wow" (Video) EU CD single # "Wow" — 3:16 # "Can't Get You Out of My Head (Greg Kurstin Remix)" — 4:05 Digital download 1 # "Wow" — 3:13 # "2 Hearts" (Mark Brown's Pacha Ibiza Upper Terrace Mix) - 7:02 Digital download 2 # "Wow" — 3:13 # "Do It Again" — 3:21 # "Carried Away" — 3:14 # "Cherry Bomb" - 4:16 Digital download 3 # "Wow" — 3:16 # "Wow" (CSS Mix) — 3:14 # "Wow" (MSTRKRFT Remix) - 4:45 # "Wow" (F*** Me I'm Famous Remix by David Guetta & Joachim Garraud) - 6:22 # "Wow" (Death Metal Disco Scene Mix) — 6:27 ==References== Category:2008 songs Category:Kylie Minogue songs Category:Dance-pop songs Category:Bubblegum pop songs
